  All rights granted under this License are granted for the term of
copyright on the Program, and are irrevocable provided the stated
conditions are met.  This License explicitly affirms your unlimited
permission to run the unmodified Program.  The output from running a
covered work is covered by this License only if the output, given its
content, constitutes a covered work.  This License acknowledges your
rights of fair use or other equivalent, as provided by copyright law.

  Subject to the above terms and conditions, you have the following
permissions.  You may convey or run a covered work in source or object
form, provided that you also do one of these things:

  a) Convey the source code in physical product, or in physical medium,
     commonly used for software interchange.

  b) Use a suitable shared library mechanism for linking with the
     Library.  A suitable mechanism is one that (1) uses at run time a
     copy of the library already present on the user's computer system,
     rather than copying library functions into the executable, and (2)
     will operate properly with a modified version of the library, if
     the user installs one, as long as the modified version is
     interface-compatible with the version that the work was made with.

  c) Convey the work in object code form under the terms of sections 4
     and 5, provided that you also convey the Corresponding Source in
     physical product, or in physical medium, commonly used for
     software interchange.

  d) Convey the work in object code form under the terms of sections 4
     and 5, provided that you also provide the information stated in
     section 4 for the Corresponding Source.

  e) Verify that the user has already been provided with a copy of
     these materials, or that you have already sent this user a copy.

  For an executable, the required form of the "work that uses the
Library" must include any data and utility programs needed for
reproducing the executable from it, but is not normally required to
print a startup message when run.

  3. Creating a Network Use Problem.

  If you modify the Program, or a covered work, and you distribute or
otherwise convey the modified Program to others through a network
connection without providing the Corresponding Source, you must make
a reasonable effort to ensure that, by providing your modifications,
the modified Program can in turn be used by such users to generate
output or provide services to others through a network connection.

  Specifically, you must require that any user who interacts with
your modified Program through a network connection is entitled to
receive the Corresponding Source of your modified version from you.

  This requirement applies both to the modified Program as a whole,
and to all its parts, regardless of how they are combined.

